About the second comment: ideally both ODU , wson, and flexgrid should have the same groupings for the label obviously with different naming .
E.g. for flexgrid, I see flex-grid-label-range-info, as in ODU there is otn-label-range-info grouping, I see flex-grid-label-step as for ODU there is otn-label-step grouping. But for example flexgrid frequency slot , as reported in RFC7698, is defined by  nominal central frequency and slot width, while here is reported flex-grid-frequency-slot as  just M value for slot-width, that is misleading. We can take into account in l0-types-ext draft to define better the usage of all these groupings.
